1
00:00:00,700 --> 00:00:01,533
<i> Just tell us, Mrs. Almazan!</i>

2
00:00:01,533 --> 00:00:02,733
<i> Where did your son go?</i>

3
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:05,033
<i> I have no idea.</i>

4
00:00:05,033 --> 00:00:07,433
<i>If you don't believe her,
that's your problem.</i>

5
00:00:07,433 --> 00:00:09,333
<i> Leon, you need to do this.</i>

6
00:00:09,333 --> 00:00:10,733
<i>You still have
to return to them.</i>

7
00:00:12,067 --> 00:00:13,200
[SCREAMS]

8
00:00:14,467 --> 00:00:17,000
- [GRUNTS]
- [CHOKING] You're alive...

9
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:18,067
<i> Yes!</i>

10
00:00:18,067 --> 00:00:20,667
<i> This treasure
will answer a lot of things.</i>

11
00:00:20,667 --> 00:00:22,433
<i> Not just for Leon's sake...</i>

12
00:00:23,367 --> 00:00:25,600
but also for Dad and Uncle Mike.

13
00:00:25,600 --> 00:00:28,100
[BODY THUDS]

14
00:00:31,200 --> 00:00:32,233
<i> He's not answering.</i>

15
00:00:32,233 --> 00:00:33,133
[CELLPHONE RINGING]

16
00:00:33,133 --> 00:00:35,067
<i>But at least
it's ringing, right?</i>

17
00:00:35,100 --> 00:00:37,267
<i>That means he's still there.
He hasn't given up.</i>

18
00:00:45,200 --> 00:00:47,267
We need to
speed up the search.

19
00:00:47,267 --> 00:00:49,600
Time is running out,
especially for Leon.

20
00:00:49,600 --> 00:00:53,200
If Sir Henri helped Leon,

21
00:00:53,200 --> 00:00:55,633
maybe we can ask
for his help too.

22
00:00:55,633 --> 00:00:57,300
I've talked to him.

23
00:00:57,300 --> 00:00:59,333
He denies that
he helped Leon escape.

24
00:00:59,333 --> 00:01:01,733
Are you saying Leon is lying?

25
00:01:01,733 --> 00:01:04,100
That's not what he said,
Jade.

26
00:01:04,100 --> 00:01:05,533
But he won't admit
he helped Leon either.

27
00:01:05,533 --> 00:01:08,500
Of course,
he has a job to protect.

28
00:01:08,533 --> 00:01:10,200
And they probably don't have

29
00:01:10,200 --> 00:01:12,100
any solid evidence
against De La Paz yet.

30
00:01:12,733 --> 00:01:15,067
His hands are tied.

31
00:01:15,067 --> 00:01:16,667
[MARTIN] It doesn't matter
what his reasons are.

32
00:01:16,667 --> 00:01:18,033
What's clear is...

33
00:01:19,467 --> 00:01:21,400
we're on our own.

34
00:01:21,400 --> 00:01:24,267
We can't count on
Sir Henri to help us.

35
00:01:25,533 --> 00:01:27,067
At least for now.

36
00:01:28,333 --> 00:01:30,400
That's fine.
We can do this.

37
00:01:30,400 --> 00:01:32,267
[LUNA] Here.
We've printed them.

38
00:01:34,700 --> 00:01:38,333
Gio and I found this
engraved on a tombstone.

39
00:01:38,333 --> 00:01:41,067
We saw this on a marker.

40
00:01:41,100 --> 00:01:42,200
Engraved in stone.

41
00:01:42,200 --> 00:01:43,033
This too.

42
00:01:43,033 --> 00:01:46,100
This is the map
Cheska gave me.

43
00:01:46,100 --> 00:01:49,133
[CHESKA] We found that
at Juan's house.

44
00:01:51,433 --> 00:01:55,733
The grave owner said
his grandmother told him

45
00:01:55,733 --> 00:01:59,267
the treasure is called
Oro Viejo.

46
00:01:59,267 --> 00:02:02,300
It looks like
these form a map.

47
00:02:02,300 --> 00:02:03,567
It's like a puzzle.

48
00:02:04,800 --> 00:02:06,300
A puzzle?

49
00:02:08,100 --> 00:02:09,333
But, wait...

50
00:02:09,800 --> 00:02:13,533
This doesn't connect
with the other pieces.

51
00:02:13,533 --> 00:02:15,700
[JUSTIN] Why does Sandro's piece
seem out of place?

52
00:02:17,767 --> 00:02:19,233
Because there's
a missing piece.

53
00:02:20,700 --> 00:02:23,733
Jade and I
haven't found our piece yet.

54
00:02:23,733 --> 00:02:29,867
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

55
00:02:29,867 --> 00:02:31,233
I got it!

56
00:02:31,233 --> 00:02:33,467
Kiko, follow me!
Follow me, guys!

57
00:02:33,467 --> 00:02:34,600
Come on.

58
00:02:35,600 --> 00:02:42,567
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

59
00:03:35,533 --> 00:03:36,600
There's a map here!

60
00:03:36,600 --> 00:03:37,900
- Right there!
- Yes!

61
00:03:38,667 --> 00:03:40,500
- Wait.
- Look.

62
00:03:41,200 --> 00:03:44,933
We need to find the section
that matches this map.

63
00:03:44,933 --> 00:03:46,867
Yes. Let's start at the bottom.

64
00:03:46,867 --> 00:03:48,500
Move it up.

65
00:03:48,500 --> 00:03:49,533
Wait.

66
00:03:49,533 --> 00:03:50,533
Keep going.

67
00:03:51,667 --> 00:03:53,500
- This! This is it!
- That's it!

68
00:03:53,500 --> 00:03:55,200
- They're identical!
- Yes, wait.

69
00:03:55,233 --> 00:03:57,233
- Take the map down!
- I got it.

70
00:03:57,233 --> 00:03:58,400
Put it on the bed!

71
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:07,767
Hand it over, Raphie.

72
00:04:08,633 --> 00:04:09,900
Hand what over?

73
00:04:09,900 --> 00:04:11,233
[MOUTH CLICKS]

74
00:04:11,233 --> 00:04:13,833
Get the two loaves of bread
you hid in your room.

75
00:04:13,833 --> 00:04:15,000
[SCOFFS]
Excuse me?

76
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:18,000
Why would I
hide bread in my room?

77
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:19,867
[MONETTE]
Oh, come on, Raphie.

78
00:04:19,867 --> 00:04:21,267
- What?
- Don't deny it.

79
00:04:21,267 --> 00:04:22,400
You've done this before.

80
00:04:22,400 --> 00:04:23,133
[RAPHIE] Uh--

81
00:04:23,133 --> 00:04:25,333
b-but that was only one time.

82
00:04:25,333 --> 00:04:28,000
After you scolded me,
I didn't do it again.

83
00:04:28,033 --> 00:04:29,033
What?

84
00:04:29,033 --> 00:04:31,267
We're missing
canned goods too.

85
00:04:31,267 --> 00:04:33,267
Oh, Monette, don't tell me
you think I took those too?

86
00:04:33,267 --> 00:04:35,633
I'm not a thief.

87
00:04:35,633 --> 00:04:37,000
I don't know
where they went!

88
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:39,633
I don't know
who would steal food.

89
00:04:39,633 --> 00:04:41,467
[CELLPHONE RINGING]

90
00:04:42,333 --> 00:04:43,933
- [RINGING CONTINUES]
- Oh!

91
00:04:43,933 --> 00:04:46,400
Maybe it's the thief.

92
00:04:46,400 --> 00:04:48,533
Who's calling?
Why aren't you answering it?

93
00:04:48,533 --> 00:04:49,533
Uh... [MOUTH CLICKS]

94
00:04:49,533 --> 00:04:52,033
Ask Cesar if he knows
who took the bread.

95
00:04:52,033 --> 00:04:54,567
- Go on. Ask him.
- I will.

96
00:04:54,567 --> 00:04:55,800
- I'll find out...
- Now, okay?

97
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:58,233
- ...who stole the bread.
- You go do that.

98
00:04:58,767 --> 00:04:59,767
[CELLPHONE BEEPS]

99
00:05:01,767 --> 00:05:02,667
Okay.

100
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:05,367
That's right.

101
00:05:05,367 --> 00:05:08,333
[INTRIGUING MUSIC PLAYING]

102
00:05:08,333 --> 00:05:09,400
Is this the other one?

103
00:05:09,400 --> 00:05:11,633
- Yeah.
- Help me.

104
00:05:11,633 --> 00:05:13,500
Okay.
It has three sections...

105
00:05:13,500 --> 00:05:16,300
and a corner
that has a tail?

106
00:05:16,300 --> 00:05:18,733
- It dips in here.
- It does.

107
00:05:19,400 --> 00:05:20,467
[KIKO] Try the bottom part.

108
00:05:20,467 --> 00:05:22,933
- It's upside down.
- No, no.

109
00:05:22,933 --> 00:05:25,033
- Here.
- There, Martin.

110
00:05:26,667 --> 00:05:28,333
- Three sections...
- That's it.

111
00:05:28,333 --> 00:05:29,433
- This is it!
- We found it.

112
00:05:29,433 --> 00:05:30,900
- Look.
- Where?

113
00:05:30,900 --> 00:05:34,800
[INTRIGUING MUSIC CONTINUES]

114
00:05:34,833 --> 00:05:37,100
- We got it.
- Right here.

115
00:05:37,100 --> 00:05:41,000
[INTRIGUING MUSIC CONTINUES]

116
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:43,000
Okay, but why are they apart?

117
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:47,733
[INTRIGUING MUSIC CONTINUES]

118
00:05:47,733 --> 00:05:49,533
What about this?

119
00:05:49,533 --> 00:05:51,333
- Let's see.
- Wait.

120
00:05:51,333 --> 00:05:52,400
- Here.
- Let me see.

121
00:05:55,033 --> 00:05:57,333
That's just a map of Hotel 88.

122
00:05:57,333 --> 00:05:58,433
So, it's useless?

123
00:05:59,033 --> 00:06:00,533
We've already been there,

124
00:06:00,533 --> 00:06:01,900
but we found nothing.

125
00:06:01,900 --> 00:06:04,500
I really think there's
still something here.

126
00:06:04,500 --> 00:06:07,033
Alright,
I'll put it away for now.

127
00:06:07,033 --> 00:06:10,567
I think the answer
to our questions

128
00:06:10,600 --> 00:06:13,867
lies in the missing map piece.

129
00:06:13,867 --> 00:06:20,133
Now we have to
match the maps by shape.

130
00:06:20,133 --> 00:06:21,767
Smart move, sis!

131
00:06:22,600 --> 00:06:27,500
But I still don't know
what the X marks.

132
00:06:29,500 --> 00:06:31,567
You still did good.

133
00:06:32,767 --> 00:06:34,900
[JADE] But "X" marks what?

134
00:06:34,900 --> 00:06:36,667
Do we have to go there?

135
00:06:36,667 --> 00:06:40,967
[MARTIN] We won't know
until we find the book.

136
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:43,767
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

137
00:06:43,767 --> 00:06:44,733
So...

138
00:06:45,667 --> 00:06:46,600
what?

139
00:06:47,433 --> 00:06:48,800
We're at a dead end?

140
00:06:51,900 --> 00:06:56,133
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

141
00:06:58,067 --> 00:07:03,700
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

142
00:07:03,700 --> 00:07:05,767
[PLASTIC RUSTLING]

143
00:07:07,933 --> 00:07:10,433
[WIRE CLANKING]

144
00:07:11,767 --> 00:07:15,733
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

145
00:07:15,767 --> 00:07:17,133
[CHAINS RATTLING]

146
00:07:22,100 --> 00:07:29,067
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

147
00:07:33,733 --> 00:07:35,767
What are you
going to do with me?

148
00:07:35,767 --> 00:07:39,700
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

149
00:07:41,767 --> 00:07:43,067
Are you going to kill me...

150
00:07:45,533 --> 00:07:47,100
...to get revenge?

151
00:07:48,833 --> 00:07:52,867
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

152
00:07:52,867 --> 00:07:55,133
Let me make myself clear.

153
00:07:55,133 --> 00:07:58,133
I didn't kill Juan.

154
00:07:59,733 --> 00:08:02,233
Uncle Andy and
his cop accomplice

155
00:08:02,233 --> 00:08:04,700
were the ones who killed Juan!

156
00:08:04,700 --> 00:08:06,067
Do you hear me?!

157
00:08:07,533 --> 00:08:10,000
I didn't kill Juan!

158
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:12,733
Andy Arellano killed Juan!

159
00:08:13,700 --> 00:08:16,500
I didn't kill Juan!

160
00:08:16,500 --> 00:08:20,033
Andy Arellano killed Juan!

161
00:08:20,033 --> 00:08:21,900
Andy Arellano killed Juan!

162
00:08:21,933 --> 00:08:23,700
- [BLADE SWOOSHES]
- [STEEL CLANKS]

163
00:08:23,700 --> 00:08:24,900
Shut the hell up!

164
00:08:24,900 --> 00:08:28,500
[MUSIC TURNS TENSE]

165
00:08:28,500 --> 00:08:30,567
Not another word.

166
00:08:31,233 --> 00:08:38,167
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

167
00:08:52,800 --> 00:08:57,633
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

168
00:08:58,967 --> 00:09:00,267
They tailed me and Luna.

169
00:09:00,867 --> 00:09:02,533
And Leon managed to escape.

170
00:09:03,233 --> 00:09:05,100
This means we have to do better

171
00:09:05,100 --> 00:09:07,433
to keep putting pressure
on Andy.

172
00:09:08,367 --> 00:09:09,467
Do better?

173
00:09:10,033 --> 00:09:11,233
How?

174
00:09:11,433 --> 00:09:13,433
We already told them
we have clues. What else?

175
00:09:14,500 --> 00:09:16,100
We can trick him.

176
00:09:16,100 --> 00:09:17,267
Trick him?

177
00:09:17,467 --> 00:09:19,200
That we already got
the treasure?

178
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:21,800
[GIO] To push his buttons.

179
00:09:22,267 --> 00:09:23,333
Merely just giving him clues
is different

180
00:09:23,333 --> 00:09:25,567
versus when the treasure
is right in front of him.

181
00:09:25,567 --> 00:09:27,367
Then this means the danger
we're facing

182
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:28,833
is even greater.

183
00:09:29,433 --> 00:09:30,533
And at that point,

184
00:09:30,533 --> 00:09:33,467
we could make him admit
to all his wrongdoings.

185
00:09:33,467 --> 00:09:35,600
[JUSTIN BREATHES HEAVILY]

186
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:36,933
[JUSTIN] Fine.

187
00:09:37,400 --> 00:09:39,100
So, how do we do it exactly?

188
00:09:39,933 --> 00:09:41,100
We'll hold a party.

189
00:09:41,467 --> 00:09:42,800
A celebration.

190
00:09:43,433 --> 00:09:45,967
While Leon's missing? Really?

191
00:09:46,167 --> 00:09:47,100
That's the point.

192
00:09:47,100 --> 00:09:49,133
He'll think that while Leon's
missing

193
00:09:49,133 --> 00:09:50,500
we're out here partying.

194
00:09:51,033 --> 00:09:53,333
It could mean that we've already
found the treasure.

195
00:09:54,233 --> 00:09:55,333
[SOFT THUD]

196
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:02,233
What about you, Kiko?

197
00:10:03,067 --> 00:10:04,300
What do you think?

198
00:10:08,633 --> 00:10:10,333
I'm sorry, Jade.

199
00:10:12,967 --> 00:10:15,300
But before we continue, maybe...

200
00:10:16,167 --> 00:10:18,233
you should tell them the truth.

201
00:10:18,867 --> 00:10:24,067
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

202
00:10:24,067 --> 00:10:25,200
What truth?

203
00:10:30,367 --> 00:10:31,500
Jade.

204
00:10:37,133 --> 00:10:38,200
[SOFT THUD]

205
00:10:38,200 --> 00:10:39,267
I'll say it.

206
00:10:41,067 --> 00:10:43,500
Jade... told Edward

207
00:10:43,500 --> 00:10:45,633
- that we're suspecting Andy.
- [RATTLES]

208
00:10:46,933 --> 00:10:49,100
[KIKO] As well as about
the treasure.

209
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:56,567
- You told him?!
- Justin.

210
00:10:56,567 --> 00:10:58,567
What if Edward told Andy
about everything?!

211
00:10:59,067 --> 00:11:00,900
Jade, what is Kiko
talking about?

212
00:11:01,533 --> 00:11:03,533
Edward won't betray us.

213
00:11:03,533 --> 00:11:04,667
Why did you do that?!

214
00:11:04,667 --> 00:11:06,067
That's enough, Justin!

215
00:11:06,067 --> 00:11:08,067
[JUSTIN] Don't tell me
you brought him in your search?

216
00:11:10,333 --> 00:11:13,200
Justin, he also wants to know
the truth about his father.

217
00:11:13,200 --> 00:11:16,167
That's enough. It's all
in the past now.

218
00:11:17,500 --> 00:11:19,067
[SLAMS]

219
00:11:19,067 --> 00:11:20,433
How stupid of you, Jade!

220
00:11:20,433 --> 00:11:21,933
[LUNA] Justin, that's enough!

221
00:11:21,933 --> 00:11:24,367
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

222
00:11:24,367 --> 00:11:25,667
[JUSTIN] You know what, Jade,

223
00:11:26,133 --> 00:11:27,367
make up your mind.

224
00:11:27,600 --> 00:11:29,400
If you still want to be
a part of this,

225
00:11:30,067 --> 00:11:32,967
you can't say anything to Edward
from now on.

226
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:35,600
[LUNA] Justin is right, Jade.

227
00:11:35,600 --> 00:11:38,133
It's not just our family
working on this.

228
00:11:38,133 --> 00:11:39,533
Gio's too.

229
00:11:39,533 --> 00:11:42,167
Everything we do affects them.

230
00:11:42,200 --> 00:11:49,133
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

231
00:11:55,533 --> 00:11:58,600
- [PHONE CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]
- [PAPER RUSTLING]

232
00:11:58,600 --> 00:12:01,367
[RAPHIE] Monette, Cesar
was asking how to--

233
00:12:03,067 --> 00:12:04,333
What were you doing?!

234
00:12:04,333 --> 00:12:05,367
Raphie!

235
00:12:05,733 --> 00:12:08,133
[PAPERS RUSTLING]

236
00:12:08,133 --> 00:12:10,267
Why were you taking photos?
Are you posting them?

237
00:12:10,267 --> 00:12:12,233
No! No, I won't!

238
00:12:15,167 --> 00:12:16,100
Delete it!

239
00:12:16,100 --> 00:12:18,767
- Come on, Monette!
- I don't want to!

240
00:12:18,767 --> 00:12:21,200
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

241
00:12:21,200 --> 00:12:23,033
I should've done this
a long time ago.

242
00:12:24,267 --> 00:12:26,967
I should've supported
your dream a long time ago.

243
00:12:28,600 --> 00:12:30,133
What are you even saying?

244
00:12:31,567 --> 00:12:33,500
Didn't I tell you
this is just a hobby?

245
00:12:33,500 --> 00:12:34,700
I'm not serious about it.

246
00:12:34,700 --> 00:12:36,233
How could you say that?

247
00:12:36,500 --> 00:12:39,333
Come on, Raphie! Look at it!

248
00:12:39,567 --> 00:12:41,433
Your works are beautiful!

249
00:12:42,333 --> 00:12:43,767
Isn't it why you received
a scholarship

250
00:12:43,767 --> 00:12:45,367
from design school back then?

251
00:12:45,367 --> 00:12:47,333
- That was before!
- [THUDS]

252
00:12:47,333 --> 00:12:50,000
And I told you, I'm just
doing this for fun!

253
00:12:50,567 --> 00:12:52,267
You know that's not true.

254
00:12:53,433 --> 00:12:54,667
Raphie.

255
00:12:55,133 --> 00:12:57,100
Raphie, I reached out to them.

256
00:12:57,100 --> 00:12:59,567
They said you can apply
for the scholarship again!

257
00:13:01,200 --> 00:13:02,733
You called the school?

258
00:13:04,433 --> 00:13:05,567
Yes.

259
00:13:06,567 --> 00:13:08,167
I gave them a call because...

260
00:13:08,567 --> 00:13:11,033
your talent shouldn't go
to waste, Raphie!

261
00:13:12,067 --> 00:13:13,167
[SARCASTICALLY] Wow!

262
00:13:13,500 --> 00:13:15,133
Way to go, Monette!

263
00:13:16,533 --> 00:13:18,267
Stop deciding for me!

264
00:13:19,433 --> 00:13:21,567
You didn't even ask
for my opinion.

265
00:13:21,600 --> 00:13:23,467
But you still want to,
don't you?

266
00:13:24,133 --> 00:13:26,467
Because you're still doing it
albeit secretly!

267
00:13:26,800 --> 00:13:29,267
But it's something
I should decide for myself!

268
00:13:30,100 --> 00:13:32,067
You're not the one
who'll do the studying!

269
00:13:33,367 --> 00:13:35,200
You're not the one
who's gonna leave.

270
00:13:35,767 --> 00:13:37,200
Raphie!

271
00:13:38,700 --> 00:13:40,167
Raphie!

272
00:13:40,633 --> 00:13:42,700
I just want to support you.

273
00:13:43,433 --> 00:13:45,367
Don't ever go through
my things again.

274
00:13:45,367 --> 00:13:52,300
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

275
00:13:53,367 --> 00:13:54,633
So, going back,

276
00:13:55,867 --> 00:13:59,167
we'll hold a celebration
to make Andy think

277
00:13:59,500 --> 00:14:00,833
that we've already found
the treasure.

278
00:14:00,833 --> 00:14:02,800
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

279
00:14:02,800 --> 00:14:05,767
Isn't it better to pay our debt
to him instead?

280
00:14:06,500 --> 00:14:08,167
The money he paid to the bank.

281
00:14:09,333 --> 00:14:10,767
I'll talk to Mom.

282
00:14:11,167 --> 00:14:13,767
We can contribute some money
but I'm not sure it's enough.

283
00:14:14,433 --> 00:14:16,600
[MARTIN] I have an idea
but I have to talk

284
00:14:16,600 --> 00:14:17,667
to Trixie first.

285
00:14:18,733 --> 00:14:20,300
[INHALES SHARPLY]

286
00:14:20,300 --> 00:14:22,833
- You'll ask for her help?
- [EXHALES DEEPLY]

287
00:14:25,733 --> 00:14:27,100
You sure about this?

288
00:14:28,233 --> 00:14:29,433
It's a long shot.

289
00:14:29,700 --> 00:14:31,400
But I'll give it a try.

290
00:14:37,300 --> 00:14:38,467
Sorry, Martin.

291
00:14:39,300 --> 00:14:40,400
Kiko.

292
00:14:40,733 --> 00:14:41,900
It's okay.

293
00:14:41,900 --> 00:14:48,833
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

294
00:15:04,100 --> 00:15:06,500
[MARTIN] There will be
a toiletry delivery.

295
00:15:06,500 --> 00:15:08,500
You and Kiko will handle it.

296
00:15:08,500 --> 00:15:11,000
Make sure the staff incentives
are included in the payroll.

297
00:15:12,767 --> 00:15:14,100
[MARTIN] Am I
missing something?

298
00:15:14,100 --> 00:15:15,700
[SARI] No, sir.

299
00:15:15,700 --> 00:15:17,033
Apart from instructions,

300
00:15:17,033 --> 00:15:19,700
you also left a to-do list
on your table.

301
00:15:20,467 --> 00:15:23,633
That's why I'm sure Sir Kiko
and I won't forget anything.

302
00:15:24,233 --> 00:15:26,067
Yes, sorry.

303
00:15:26,067 --> 00:15:28,833
I want to make sure everything's
set before I go back to Manila.

304
00:15:29,500 --> 00:15:32,033
Sir, you won't be there
for a day.

305
00:15:32,033 --> 00:15:34,067
Don't worry about the hotel.

306
00:15:34,067 --> 00:15:38,167
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

307
00:15:38,200 --> 00:15:40,967
Would you like me to go
with you and Ms. Trixie?

308
00:15:41,733 --> 00:15:43,667
You know I'm
a great chaperon.

309
00:15:45,533 --> 00:15:47,000
Who knows...

310
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:48,933
- I might charm your stepdad.
- No.

311
00:15:49,700 --> 00:15:51,800
He might say something
bad about you.

312
00:15:52,533 --> 00:15:54,033
I'll definitely talk back.

313
00:15:54,033 --> 00:16:01,033
[BRIGHT MUSIC PLAYING]

314
00:16:09,300 --> 00:16:11,600
You don't have to do that, sir.

315
00:16:13,733 --> 00:16:15,033
Don't worry, sir.

316
00:16:15,767 --> 00:16:17,233
I have a
solution for that.

317
00:16:19,300 --> 00:16:22,267
[SARI] Take this fan with you.

318
00:16:23,033 --> 00:16:25,800
So that when your stepdad
is getting mad,

319
00:16:25,800 --> 00:16:27,767
you can just fan him
to help him calm down

320
00:16:27,767 --> 00:16:29,933
[BOTH CHUCKLES]

321
00:16:33,033 --> 00:16:35,000
You really are
my happy pill, Sari.

322
00:16:36,667 --> 00:16:37,933
Thank you.

323
00:16:37,933 --> 00:16:44,667
[BRIGHT MUSIC CONTINUES]

324
00:16:47,800 --> 00:16:51,000
Why do you have to loan that
much money from the company?

325
00:16:51,000 --> 00:16:54,700
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

326
00:16:54,700 --> 00:16:56,067
Mom...

327
00:16:56,067 --> 00:16:58,167
we have to pay Uncle Andy.

328
00:16:59,033 --> 00:17:01,800
He helped us pay off
our debt at the hotel.

329
00:17:02,633 --> 00:17:04,667
[JUSTIN] But it was fake, Mom.

330
00:17:04,667 --> 00:17:06,567
He just wanted a
partnership with the hotel,

331
00:17:06,567 --> 00:17:08,300
because he had
a different agenda.

332
00:17:08,300 --> 00:17:09,833
What agenda?

333
00:17:09,833 --> 00:17:11,700
[LUNA] He doesn't want
any competition, Ma.

334
00:17:12,267 --> 00:17:15,033
He wants to monopolize
everything in this island.

335
00:17:15,067 --> 00:17:17,800
[SIGHS] That's why he wants
to take the hotel

336
00:17:17,800 --> 00:17:19,200
that Dad left us with.

337
00:17:19,200 --> 00:17:22,233
Andy really wants to corner you.

338
00:17:22,233 --> 00:17:25,367
And it's possible
that he set up Leon.

339
00:17:25,367 --> 00:17:27,633
Just to get the partnership!

340
00:17:27,633 --> 00:17:28,900
Yes.

341
00:17:28,900 --> 00:17:30,767
We just can't prove it.

342
00:17:32,033 --> 00:17:33,300
[SIGHS]

343
00:17:33,300 --> 00:17:34,667
[LUNA] Ma...

344
00:17:34,667 --> 00:17:36,033
no matter how much
you lend us,

345
00:17:36,033 --> 00:17:37,700
that's already a huge help
for the hotel.

346
00:17:39,867 --> 00:17:41,700
It's okay, don't worry about it.

347
00:17:41,700 --> 00:17:43,767
I will speak to the
Finance Officer.

348
00:17:43,767 --> 00:17:46,167
I'll ask him where
we could get funds

349
00:17:46,167 --> 00:17:47,867
from our other businesses.

350
00:17:49,367 --> 00:17:50,833
Thank you so much, Ma.

351
00:17:51,700 --> 00:17:53,000
Thank you so much.

352
00:17:54,867 --> 00:17:56,333
It's okay.

353
00:17:56,333 --> 00:17:59,833
[FRIDA] Don't worry about it.
I'll help you

354
00:17:59,833 --> 00:18:01,933
Just don't get involved
with Andy.

355
00:18:04,133 --> 00:18:06,000
[MARTIN] Thank you.

356
00:18:09,100 --> 00:18:12,367
So, you dragged me out here
to ask for money.

357
00:18:13,933 --> 00:18:16,633
Carlos, your tone please.

358
00:18:16,633 --> 00:18:19,133
We haven't seen
our children for a while.

359
00:18:19,133 --> 00:18:21,033
That's the thing.

360
00:18:21,033 --> 00:18:22,967
[CARLOS] They've only
shown up now,

361
00:18:23,000 --> 00:18:24,300
and it's just for money.

362
00:18:25,367 --> 00:18:28,433
Dad, we're asking
for your help because

363
00:18:28,433 --> 00:18:30,800
we know that you can help us.

364
00:18:30,800 --> 00:18:32,800
Of course I can!

365
00:18:32,800 --> 00:18:35,067
But not necessarily, I will.

366
00:18:36,800 --> 00:18:38,833
I won't give you any money

367
00:18:38,833 --> 00:18:40,667
for that hotel.

368
00:18:40,667 --> 00:18:43,367
This isn't a handout,
it's a loan.

369
00:18:43,367 --> 00:18:46,167
A loan.
We can do it on your terms.

370
00:18:46,167 --> 00:18:48,100
[CHUCKLES] Alright.

371
00:18:49,400 --> 00:18:51,000
How will you pay me back?

372
00:18:52,667 --> 00:18:54,233
[CARLOS] You know that
the hotel...

373
00:18:54,233 --> 00:18:56,167
is already on the
losing end.

374
00:18:56,900 --> 00:18:58,467
Didn't I tell you that
a long time ago?

375
00:18:58,467 --> 00:19:00,367
I need to take the risk
for this business

376
00:19:00,367 --> 00:19:02,433
for my brothers.

377
00:19:02,433 --> 00:19:04,367
I'm doing this for my family.

378
00:19:04,367 --> 00:19:06,000
[CARLOS] No!

379
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:07,333
[LOUISE] Carlos.

380
00:19:09,300 --> 00:19:11,733
[TRIXIE] Then I want
my inheritance.

381
00:19:11,733 --> 00:19:13,133
Trixie!

382
00:19:15,267 --> 00:19:16,967
Yes, Dad.

383
00:19:16,967 --> 00:19:18,800
If you won't lent Martin money,

384
00:19:18,800 --> 00:19:20,200
then I'll take it
from my inheritance.

385
00:19:20,200 --> 00:19:21,433
[CARLOS] No!

386
00:19:21,433 --> 00:19:24,933
[Carlos] If you insist
on helping Martin,

387
00:19:24,933 --> 00:19:27,733
then don't
go back to our house.

388
00:19:27,733 --> 00:19:30,267
- Both of you!
- Carlos, it's Trixie!

389
00:19:31,900 --> 00:19:33,167
Louise.

390
00:19:33,167 --> 00:19:34,367
Let's go!

391
00:19:38,833 --> 00:19:39,933
Go ahead.

392
00:19:41,333 --> 00:19:43,333
I want to be with my children.

393
00:19:43,333 --> 00:19:50,267
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

394
00:19:50,800 --> 00:19:52,300
Mom, you should go with Dad.

395
00:19:55,367 --> 00:19:56,833
How much, Martin?

396
00:19:57,500 --> 00:19:58,967
I will help you.

397
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:01,333
Mom, are you sure?

398
00:20:02,933 --> 00:20:04,733
You might end up
fighting with Dad.

399
00:20:05,900 --> 00:20:07,833
I have funds that your dad
doesn't know about.

400
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:10,433
You can use that.

401
00:20:14,800 --> 00:20:21,833
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

402
00:20:21,833 --> 00:20:25,000
I should have stood up
for you a long time ago, Martin.

403
00:20:26,333 --> 00:20:28,500
This is the least that I can do.

404
00:20:29,433 --> 00:20:31,833
I will help your family.

405
00:20:34,967 --> 00:20:36,333
Thank you, Ma.

406
00:20:36,333 --> 00:20:43,333
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

407
00:20:58,967 --> 00:21:05,933
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

408
00:21:09,833 --> 00:21:11,500
[CHESKA] Pst! Hey, Trixie!

409
00:21:11,500 --> 00:21:12,733
What are you doing?

410
00:21:12,733 --> 00:21:14,367
Nothing.

411
00:21:15,200 --> 00:21:16,733
You're lying.
What were you doing?

412
00:21:18,733 --> 00:21:19,967
[SIGHS]

413
00:21:19,967 --> 00:21:22,067
I just missed something.

414
00:21:22,067 --> 00:21:23,767
Hmm. Who?

415
00:21:24,600 --> 00:21:26,767
- Shut up.
- [CHUCKLES]

416
00:21:28,167 --> 00:21:30,033
- Who is it?
- Enough!

417
00:21:34,200 --> 00:21:36,700
You know that feeling where...

418
00:21:36,700 --> 00:21:39,633
you thought someone didn't
mean anything to you,

419
00:21:40,500 --> 00:21:42,933
[TRIXIE] but one day
when you wake up,

420
00:21:42,967 --> 00:21:45,100
you realize that...

421
00:21:45,100 --> 00:21:47,167
your perspective
on them has changed.

422
00:21:48,700 --> 00:21:50,000
Yes.

423
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:51,200
I get you.

424
00:21:52,200 --> 00:21:53,767
I get how you feel.

425
00:21:54,633 --> 00:21:55,900
I can relate to that.

426
00:21:57,133 --> 00:21:59,700
- Really?
- I was like that too.

427
00:21:59,700 --> 00:22:01,000
With who?

428
00:22:03,200 --> 00:22:04,933
[LAUGHS]

429
00:22:04,933 --> 00:22:11,933
[BRIGHT MUSIC PLAYING]

430
00:22:21,100 --> 00:22:23,067
[MARTIN EXHALES] Finally!

431
00:22:23,067 --> 00:22:25,800
We've managed to raise
the money to pay Andy.

432
00:22:25,800 --> 00:22:27,233
Thanks to Aunt Frida.

433
00:22:27,833 --> 00:22:30,233
Thank you to your mom too,
Martin and Trixie.

434
00:22:30,833 --> 00:22:32,600
The check has been settled.

435
00:22:32,600 --> 00:22:34,700
This is the file that
Andy needs to sign

436
00:22:34,700 --> 00:22:36,700
as proof that we have paid him.

437
00:22:36,700 --> 00:22:38,133
Now.

438
00:22:38,133 --> 00:22:40,500
How will we give this to him?

439
00:22:40,500 --> 00:22:41,867
I'll meet him.

440
00:22:43,600 --> 00:22:45,000
No.

441
00:22:45,000 --> 00:22:47,567
I'll meet him.
He might do something to you

442
00:22:48,300 --> 00:22:49,900
[JUSTIN] I'll go with you.

443
00:22:51,633 --> 00:22:53,033
I'll go with Luna.

444
00:22:53,033 --> 00:22:54,867
- But...
- Don't worry, Gio.

445
00:22:54,867 --> 00:22:56,800
I won't let him hurt my sister.

446
00:23:00,733 --> 00:23:01,900
Gio, it's alright.

447
00:23:01,900 --> 00:23:06,067
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

448
00:23:06,067 --> 00:23:07,233
Fine.

449
00:23:09,033 --> 00:23:10,633
Sure, but because
that's the plan,

450
00:23:10,633 --> 00:23:12,633
he needs to think that we
have a lot of money.

451
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:16,700
And he should feel that we're
hiding something from him.

452
00:23:19,300 --> 00:23:21,267
You're paying me?

453
00:23:21,267 --> 00:23:22,633
Yes.

454
00:23:23,700 --> 00:23:25,533
Please sign the agreement.

455
00:23:27,600 --> 00:23:28,967
[JUSTIN] It is clear that

456
00:23:28,967 --> 00:23:31,667
you have received money
from us as payment

457
00:23:31,667 --> 00:23:34,567
For the money you paid
at Hotel 88.

458
00:23:37,667 --> 00:23:39,233
The hotel has money.

459
00:23:40,567 --> 00:23:42,200
You can say that...

460
00:23:42,200 --> 00:23:43,833
we got lucky.

461
00:23:46,567 --> 00:23:47,833
[CHUCKLES]

462
00:23:47,833 --> 00:23:48,900
Lucky?

463
00:23:48,900 --> 00:23:51,000
[LUNA] It doesn't matter
where we got the money.

464
00:23:51,000 --> 00:23:53,067
What's important is we're
paying you back.

465
00:23:53,067 --> 00:23:58,867
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES, FADES]

466
00:23:59,933 --> 00:24:01,833
Even if you kill me...

467
00:24:03,100 --> 00:24:05,567
I didn't kill Juan..

468
00:24:08,667 --> 00:24:10,333
[LEON] It's Andy Arellano.

469
00:24:12,200 --> 00:24:13,867
Because of the treasure.

470
00:24:13,867 --> 00:24:18,367
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

471
00:24:18,367 --> 00:24:20,233
I know about the treasure.

472
00:24:21,733 --> 00:24:23,167
Andy knows.

473
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:25,333
Juan knew about it too.

474
00:24:27,600 --> 00:24:29,133
And my father knew about it too.

475
00:24:29,167 --> 00:24:35,633
[UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES]

476
00:24:35,633 --> 00:24:38,833
[LEON] That's why you
beat them up when I saw you.

477
00:24:40,900 --> 00:24:42,333
Because of the treasure.

478
00:24:43,667 --> 00:24:45,133
Right?

479
00:24:47,000 --> 00:24:48,933
[LEON] You burned down
the hotel.

480
00:24:49,900 --> 00:24:51,367
For the treasure.

481
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:54,333
[LEON] Why?

482
00:24:55,833 --> 00:24:58,167
Why do you want
to get the money?

483
00:24:59,267 --> 00:25:00,833
To be rich?

484
00:25:03,967 --> 00:25:06,733
To the point where
you killed my dad.

485
00:25:06,733 --> 00:25:13,667
[UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES]

486
00:25:21,933 --> 00:25:28,900
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

487
00:25:34,333 --> 00:25:35,933
Luna, let's go.

488
00:25:35,967 --> 00:25:37,800
We still need to prepare
for the celebration.

489
00:25:39,800 --> 00:25:42,100
- Celebration?
- [LUNA CHUCKLES] It's nothing.

490
00:25:42,100 --> 00:25:44,367
Just ignore Justin.

491
00:25:44,367 --> 00:25:46,100
We'll head out now.

492
00:25:47,367 --> 00:25:48,933
Thank you so much.

493
00:25:49,467 --> 00:25:50,933
Thank you.

494
00:25:50,933 --> 00:25:57,900
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

495
00:26:04,833 --> 00:26:07,000
<i>Where did Jade
get the treasure?</i>

496
00:26:07,000 --> 00:26:09,700
<i>His Dad's faults
aren't Edward's faults.</i>

497
00:26:09,733 --> 00:26:11,300
<i>Then you shouldn't
have gotten mad at me</i>

498
00:26:11,300 --> 00:26:13,800
<i>when you thought Dad
killed Uncle Fred.</i>

499
00:26:13,800 --> 00:26:15,833
<i>If it's my father's fault,
it's my fault too?</i>

500
00:26:15,833 --> 00:26:17,067
<i>- If it's Edward--
- Kiko, that's different!</i>

501
00:26:17,067 --> 00:26:18,767
<i> How is that different?</i>

502
00:26:19,900 --> 00:26:21,933
<i>Juan's real murderer
just came out.</i>

503
00:26:22,433 --> 00:26:24,100
<i> Who?!</i>

504
00:26:24,100 --> 00:26:27,033
<i> The treasure needs to be mine.</i>

505
00:26:27,033 --> 00:26:30,300
<i>But first, I have one last
thing to finish.</i>

506
00:26:31,067 --> 00:26:31,833
[GROANS]
